Package gov.nasa.arc.pds.xml.generated

Class Quaternion

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.arc.pds.xml.generated.Quaternion
  • public class Quaternion
extends java.lang.Object
    The Quaternion class models a mathematical construct that consists of four individual numeric components. Quaternions are a convenient mechanism for encapsulating orientation information since they require only four units of numeric storage, as opposed to the nine needed for a rotation matrix.

    Java class for Quaternion complex type

      • getQuaternionComponents

        public java.util.List<QuaternionComponent> getQuaternionComponents()
        Gets the value of the quaternionComponents property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the quaternionComponents property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

         getQuaternionComponents().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list QuaternionComponent

        Returns:
        The value of the quaternionComponents property.
